# {{NAME}} — agent instructions

Runtime-agnostic instructions for **Codex, Cursor, and any shell-capable AI agent**.
(Claude Code reads `SKILL.md`; tool-use LLMs read `tool-schema.json`. Same skill, one behavior.)

## What this does

{{DESCRIPTION}} You bring your own key — no wallet, no MythosForge account, no payment.

## Setup

- Node 18+ (built-in `fetch`; no `npm install`).
- Export your own key: `{{PRIMARY_ENV}}` ({{ENV_LINK}}). Billed to your account.

## Run

```bash
node generate.mjs --prompt "..." --aspect landscape
```

- `--prompt` (required, ≤2000 chars)
- `--aspect` `square` (default) | `landscape` | `portrait`
- `--out <path>` optional; defaults to `out/<aspect>.{{EXT}}`
- `--dry-run` prints the request without spending or needing a key

## Result

Prints one JSON line and writes the output file:

```json
{ "ok": true, "aspect": "landscape", "prompt": "...", "path": "/abs/out/...", "bytes": 148213 }
```

Read `path`. On failure it prints `{ "ok": false, "error": "..." }` and exits non-zero. Never
claim an output exists unless `ok` was `true`.

## For hosted / tool-use LLMs (Bankr LLM, Surplus, OpenAI, Claude API)

Those models can't run a shell themselves. The host harness hands the model `tool-schema.json`
(the `openai` or `anthropic` block); when the model emits a `{{TOOL_NAME}}` tool call, the host
runs the `node generate.mjs …` command above (with `{{PRIMARY_ENV}}` set) and feeds `path` back
as the tool result.
